<p>The gap is narrowing. For most use cases outside of top-security government applications, open-source accuracy is production-ready.</p>

<h2>The Third Option: Open Core</h2>

<p>OpenBiometrics offers a unique middle ground — <strong>open core</strong>:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Free tier:</strong> Self-host with MIT license, unlimited usage</li>
  <li><strong>Cloud tier:</strong> Managed API at $29-99/month when you don't want to manage infrastructure</li>
  <li><strong>Same codebase:</strong> Migrate between self-hosted and cloud without code changes</li>
</ul>

<p>Start with the cloud API today, move to self-hosted when you scale. Or start self-hosted and add the cloud API for customers who want managed service.</p>

<h2>Decision Framework</h2>

<p>Ask these four questions:</p>

<ol>
  <li><strong>Can biometric data leave your infrastructure?</strong> If no → self-host</li>
  <li><strong>Do you need it this week?</strong> If yes → managed API</li>
  <li><strong>Is volume over 100K/month?</strong> If yes → self-host (cheaper)</li>
  <li><strong>Do you have DevOps capacity?</strong> If no → managed API</li>
</ol>

